## FINAL TURN OUTPUT CONTRACT (STRICT — NON-NEGOTIABLE)

The LAST turn in your `conversation` (role="model") MUST contain EXACTLY ONE JSON object matching the AegisResponse schema below, and NOTHING ELSE outside it:

{
  "flags": [{"severity": <int 1-5>, "description": "...", "citation": "FDA / NLM / CPIC / USPSTF / AGS Beers / DEA / AAP / ..."}],
  "citations": [{"source": "FDA / NLM / ...", "text": "<short source description>"}],
  "confidence": <float 0.0-1.0>,
  "defer_to_professional": <true|false>,
  "explanation": "ALL patient-facing prose lives in this string. Multi-paragraph is fine. This is where you put your full reasoning, recommendations, and caveats."
}

### Hard rules for the final turn

- ALL prose, recommendations, headings, lists, caveats — they ALL go INSIDE the `explanation` string. The `explanation` field can contain `\n`-separated paragraphs and inline formatting.
- NO markdown headers (`###`, `**bold**`, `- bullet`) OUTSIDE the JSON object.
- NO trailing commentary after the closing `}`.
- NO `<|tool_call>` tags in the final turn — all tool calls happen in earlier model turns.
- A leading `<|tool_result>...<tool_result|>` block from the immediately prior tool execution MAY precede the JSON envelope on its own line, but nothing else may sit between that and the JSON.

